</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11D497D7994C7CFFEBE32FC" blockId="4.[189,1399,1664,1938]" box="[234,325,1664,1690]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11D497D7994C7CFFEBE32FC" bold="true" box="[234,325,1664,1690]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11D497D79C3C7EBFCF133F7" blockId="4.[189,1399,1664,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
BODY. BL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11D497D7824C7ECFE1532D8" box="[346,494,1699,1726]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.8">4.8–5.3 mm</quantity>
. Body slightly pubescent, smooth and shiny. Head nasiform (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11D497D7C4AC7EBFED63287" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="0.83" valueMax="0.89" valueMin="0.77">0.77– 0.89 mm</quantity>
), with sparse short hairs posteriorly; eye almond-shaped, glabrous; antennal shelf strongly prominent; antenna 15-segmented, with short heterogeneous setae; scape as long as head; pedicel thinner; F1 one and a half times as long as pedicel or other flagellomeres; F2–F13 gradually lengthening; F13 tapering at apex and slightly shorter than F1 (antennomere length of 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD11D497D7D45C67FFB5E332C" box="[1083,1189,1840,1866]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.72; P-0.19; F1-0.29; F2-0.11; F3-0.12; F4-0.11; F5-0.12; F6-0.10; F7-0.11; F8-0.13; F9-0.13; F10-0.14; F11-0.15; F12-0.15; F13-0.28); mandibles simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C046FDAC36E5" blockId="5.[188,1400,265,643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
MESOSOMA. Almost as long as metasoma, flattened (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C7AE9C046FBB03545" box="[919,1099,265,291]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.76" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.62" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="1.76" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.62">1.62–1.90 mm</quantity>
); pronotum with epomia extending from front coxa to posterodorsal pronotal corners; posterior margin of pronotum curved; mesoscutum with several hairs; notauli complete and deeply impressed; scutellum without posterior scutellar pits; mesopleuron with prominent longitudinal keel; propodeum with plicae, median propodeal keel simple. Fore wing hyaline, micro-pubescent, extending beyond metasoma (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C7DC5C0D9FA9135D6" box="[1211,1386,406,432]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.26" metricValueMax="3.78" metricValueMin="2.74" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="3.26" valueMax="3.78" valueMin="2.74">2.74–3.78 mm</quantity>
); C, Sc+R, M+Cu, basal vein, marginal vein and r-rs pigmented; marginal vein shorter than its distance from basal vein; postmarginal vein barely longer than r-rs, pigmented on half length of radial cell; Rs nebulous proximally and pigmented distally from r-rs, projecting distally to postmarginal vein but fading before reaching wing margin; radial cell open. Hind wing hyaline, reduced and narrow (HwL =?– 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C79A6C309FEBC3606" box="[216,327,582,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.39" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="2.39">2.39 mm</quantity>
). Legs slender, with hind femur and coxa enlarged, covered with scattered setae; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C3E4FEB23737" blockId="5.[189,1399,682,850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
METASOMA. Petiole glabrous, longitudinally striated and with transverse keels, 1.7 times longer (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C79C0C382FED1368E" box="[190,298,717,744]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
) than wide (PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C7B68C381FD7E368E" box="[534,645,718,744]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
); gaster fusiform, depressed (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C7D52C382FB20368E" box="[1068,1243,717,744]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9249999999999998" metricValueMax="1.95" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="1.9249999999999998" valueMax="1.95" valueMin="1.9">1.90–1.95 mm</quantity>
, GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11C497C7C4AC381FED2376D" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.53" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.48">0.48– 0.58 mm</quantity>
); S2 and T2 longest, covering two-thirds of gaster, T2 striated at junction with petiole; four ringlike segments distinguishable beyond large tergite, hypopygium bearing several long setae; ovipositor not exerted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C7994C236FED137F5" blockId="5.[189,313,889,950]" box="[234,298,889,915]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7994C236FED137F5" bold="true" box="[234,298,889,915]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C2D3FEC237D0" blockId="5.[189,313,889,950]" box="[189,313,924,950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D11C497C79C3C292FCC33268" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C292FEBF3791" blockId="5.[189,324,989,1015]" box="[189,324,989,1015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
<heading id="D0A13275D11C497C79C3C292FEBF3791" bold="true" box="[189,324,989,1015]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C79C3C292FEBF3791" bold="true" box="[189,324,989,1015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C543FE2F309C" blockId="5.[187,1399,1036,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C7875C543FE443041" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[267,447,1036,1063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7881C543FCF03040" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[511,779,1036,1062]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7881C543FCF03040" box="[511,779,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11C497C7A6CC543FC953040" box="[786,878,1036,1062]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7D7FC543FBB73040" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[1025,1100,1036,1062]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7D7FC543FBB73040" box="[1025,1100,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: macropterous, notauli present, mandibles of ordinary form, scutellum without a row of foveae along posterior margin, marginal vein shorter than its distance from basal vein, pronotum elongate, without a hollow on each side (= pronotal pits), epomia present, median keel of propodeum simple, petiole more than one and a half time as long as wide. The flattened body is generally accepted to diagnose 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7855C5F3FE5730B0" box="[299,428,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7855C5F3FE8D30B0" box="[299,374,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C78C7C5F3FDB730B1" author="Macek J." box="[441,588,1212,1239]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek 1996</bibRefCitation>
) and is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7A66C5F3FBD830B0" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[792,1059,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7A66C5F3FBD830B0" box="[792,1059,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, strengthening the placement of the species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C78FCC590FE36309F" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[386,461,1247,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C78FCC590FE36309F" box="[386,461,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11C497C79C3C46FFCC33268" blockId="5.[189,1399,1312,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
Following the key to European species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7BD7C46FFD0F315C" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[681,756,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7BD7C46FFD0F315C" box="[681,756,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C7A65C46FFC38315D" author="Macek J." box="[795,963,1312,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7AB0C46FFB22315C" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[974,1241,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7AB0C46FFB22315C" box="[974,1241,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11C497C7D9EC46EFAC1315D" box="[1248,1338,1313,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out between 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C782BC40BFD6A3138" authority="Kieffer, 1916" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[341,657,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subclausa">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C782BC40BFE103138" box="[341,491,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. subclausa</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1916
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7BB2C40BFBC73138" authority="Thomson, 1858" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1858" box="[716,1084,1347,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="validicornis">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7BB2C40BFC823138" box="[716,889,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. validicornis</emphasis>
Thomson, 1858
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the first by having a marked epomia and from the second by having the median propodeal keel simple (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C7C5BC428FF0731C3" author="Macek J." pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="29 - 39" refId="ref15400" refString="Macek J. 1996. Revision of the European species of Belyta Jurine. Acta Musei Nationalis Prague, Series B, Historia Naturalis 51 (1 - 4): 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1996">Macek 1996</bibRefCitation>
). The diagnostic character for 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7B1EC4C5FC9031C2" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[608,875,1418,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7B1EC4C5FC9031C2" box="[608,875,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the curiously marked longitudinal keel on the mesopleuron, which is absent in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7A42C4E2FC7E31A1" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[828,901,1453,1479]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7A42C4E2FC7E31A1" box="[828,901,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From the Eocene of Florissant is known 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C79C1C49EFE11318D" authority="Brues, 1910" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1910" box="[191,490,1488,1515]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mortuella">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C79C1C49EFEA8318C" box="[191,339,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. mortuella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C7824C49EFE11318D" author="Brues C. T." box="[346,490,1489,1515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="3 - 125" refId="ref13960" refString="Brues C. T. 1910. The parasitic Hymenoptera of the Tertiary of Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard College 54 (1): 3 - 125. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 30208802 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Brues, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7BE9C49FFD19318C" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[663,738,1488,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7BE9C49FFD19318C" box="[663,738,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Belyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11C497C7B97C49EFCD7318D" box="[745,812,1488,1515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" sensu="lato">s. lat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), which differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11C497C7D53C49EFAF3318C" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1069,1288,1488,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Belyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knudhoejgaardi">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11C497C7D53C49EFAF3318C" box="[1069,1288,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">B. knudhoejgaardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by being shorter and having a less flattened body (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11C497C7BE0C4BBFCD03268" author="Brues C. T." box="[670,811,1524,1550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" pagination="3 - 125" refId="ref13960" refString="Brues C. T. 1910. The parasitic Hymenoptera of the Tertiary of Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard College 54 (1): 3 - 125. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 30208802 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Brues 1910</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
